-- Finance Police to Get Results of Account Checks on HSBC Swiss, Sole Says
-- Lorenzo Totaro
-- 2010-06-24T07:40:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/finance-police-to-get-results-of-account-checks-on-hsbc-swiss-sole-says.html

          
          
             Italian checks on possible tax
evasion and money laundering by account holders at  HSBC Holdings
Plc’s  Swiss private bank will yield initial results next month,
il Sole 24 Ore reported, citing the head of the finance police.  
 “We’ll get the first results by the end of July,” General
Nino Di Paolo told Sole in an interview published today. Finance
police are examining a list of some 7,000 accounts with a total
value of about $6.9 billion, he told the Italian newspaper.  
